            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48279",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=farrelley",
                        "name": "farrelley",
                        "displayName": "Shaun Farrell",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think this is fine and not any issue.  It's throwing an exceptions because there is nothing to encode.  This is a PHP null. \r\n\r\nThoughts?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=farrelley",
                        "name": "farrelley",
                        "displayName": "Shaun Farrell",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-08-29T19:29:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-08-29T19:29:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48768",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree.  Changing the behavior at this point in ZFv1's lifecycle would likely be counterproductive.  I do, however, think it's prudent that we discuss whether ZFv2's Zend\\Json should incorporate this change.  Should it align with {{json_decode}}'s behavior for consistency, or does throwing an exception make more sense?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-10-23T23:56:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-10-23T23:56:18.000+0000"
                }
            ]
